25|$|One of the {{subjects}} discussed in the literature {{is whether or not}} extreme <b>weather</b> <b>events</b> can be attributed to human activities. Seneviratne et al. (2012) stated that attributing individual extreme <b>weather</b> <b>events</b> to human activities was challenging. They were, however, more confident over attributing changes in long-term trends of extreme weather. For example, Seneviratne et al. (2012) concluded that human activities had likely led to a warming of extreme daily minimum and maximum temperatures at the global scale.|$|E
